<subSubSection id="3041A6791A1769E44CC3A454ED9FDC7E" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6D9A41E7EDA1058F19A7A6BBA3F74D52" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis id="F0947AB9167E7420EAA9E7D69A1D01D9" italics="true" pageNumber="360">Note:</emphasis>
Grant &amp; Zijlstra (in 
<emphasis id="388BB380C8D68DBDDC62FF26F891C05F" italics="true" pageNumber="360">Selbyana</emphasis>
19: 96. 1998) argue that 
<taxonomicName id="DB68B73E60053314070247316E4C184D" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karatas">
<emphasis id="96212CB73690A642BA1E5ABD148B6D22" italics="true" pageNumber="360">B. karatas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus id="FF8E62D215CC3624884EFE0C2EB16F78">generitype</typeStatus>
, the choice having been made by Regel (in 
<emphasis id="D8BBCAE30F38089D971DE08E342962D1" italics="true" pageNumber="360">Gartenflora</emphasis>
17: 67. 1868) which therefore pre-dates the more widely accepted choice of 
<taxonomicName id="415E702F86933B80CFBDA750664B5D37" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinguin">
<emphasis id="D8CCC318051FA32F000ECB3EA33906F1" italics="true" pageNumber="360">B. pinguin</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, made by Hitchcock (
<emphasis id="FBF4ECD9AB07A4477EF028171DFBF0E5" italics="true" pageNumber="360">Prop. Brit. Bot.</emphasis>
: 144. 1929).
</paragraph>
